# Content Management

## Content Centralization
- **All user-facing text** must be in `data/content.json`
- Never hardcode text in components
- Use `content` object from `@/lib/content` for all text

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
import { content } from '@/lib/content'

export const Hero = () => {
  return <h1>{content.hero.title}</h1>
}

// ❌ Incorrect
export const Hero = () => {
  return <h1>Frontend Engineer</h1> // Hardcoded text
}
```

## Content Structure
- Organize content by feature/section in `content.json`
- Include all text: labels, placeholders, error messages, aria-labels, button text
- Use descriptive keys that match component structure

## Dynamic Content
- Use `.replace()` for dynamic values in strings
- Provide template placeholders in content (e.g., `{company}`, `{title}`)

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
aria-label={content.experience.ariaLabels.company.replace('{company}', company)}
```

## What Must Be in Content
- All button labels
- All form labels and placeholders
- All error messages
- All aria-labels
- All headings and descriptions
- All navigation text
